        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Short stature-valvular heart disease-characteristic facies syndrome is characterised by severe short stature with disproportionately short legs small hands clinodactyly valvular heart disease and dysmorphism (ptosis high-arched palate abnormal dentition). It has been described in a mother and two daughters. This syndrome is probably transmitted as an autosomal dominant trait."
        },
